text: Scrying Sheets.
Anyone running it in a deck?
Not I
I currently have it in Reki because I'm running all snow lands both for Extraplanar Lens, Into the North, and Mouth of Ronom
But I honestly can't think of the last time I've actually used the ability

Now normally that wouldn't be a big deal, because there's no downside to not using it. Except there kinda is. My deck has a Vernal Bloom, the Lens, and Caged Sun, and Sheets doesn't double with them. I also have a Vorinclex and a Mana Reflection, and though it does provide double colorless there, that's less useful than double green
I'm at 35 lands, 25 forests and 10 utility, but I feel like that's maybe 1 too many utility lands.
1. Ancient Tomb 2. Dust Bowl 3. Homeward Path 4. Nykthos 5. Reliquary Tower 6. Scavernger Grounds 7. Scrying Sheets 8. Strip Mine 9. Terrain Generator 10. Untaidake the Cloud Keeper
Do you have any ways to recur lands?
You're in green and you're running Terrain Generator?
Zero recursion
Deck draws a shitload so I always have extra basics in hand
Between Sheets and Generator, Generator does a lot more work. I'd probably be fine with an Exploration
But that takes a slot

Just verified, I have literally zero graveyard interaction. Well, Hua Tuo Honored Physician, but that's only creatures, and he's getting replaced with Marwyn the Nurturer when Dominaria hits. Nothing that can interact w lands in the yard.
Hrm…with all the draw couldn’t you also consider Burgeoning?
I recognize the slot it takes, but you could simply replace Scrying Sheets, given the draw and ability to get all those lands into play.
Burgeoning is overused, but here it might make sense.

Yeah, for sure, but same thing, they take slots. I could dump a Kodama's Reach or something, but Burgeoning/Exploration are cards for when you're ahead, where as Reach and Cultivate can get you caught up if you're behind
[[Freyalise, Llanowar's Fury]] doesn't really do -that- much for me so I could pull that for something
